OL,4,Cknowingly worked for 'alleged war
OL,5,Ccriminal'
OL,7,FShe had roles in regulated financial
OL,8,Fservices on the island between 2000
OL,9,Fand 2013 before leaving and gaining
OL,10,Femployment with "Client 1" - whom she
OL,11,Fhad previously worked for - becoming
OL,12,Fhis son's personal assistant.
OL,14,FHowever, the regulator summarises that
OL,15,FMs Blondel's remit stretched far
OL,16,Fbeyond this, advising and assisting
OL,17,F"Client 1" with his business and
OL,18,Ffinancial activities.
