OL,4,Cknowingly worked for 'alleged war
OL,5,Ccriminal'
OL,7,FThis did not go ahead and Ms Blondel
OL,8,Finstead used the money to make more
OL,9,Fthan 150 payments to multiple third
OL,10,Fparties on behalf of her client.
OL,12,FThe regulator believes this "led to a
OL,13,Fvery real risk that Ms Blondel may
OL,14,Fhave been used to launder the proceeds
OL,15,Fof crime, a risk which Ms Blondel has
OL,16,Fconsistently failed to recognise".
OL,18,FIn June 2020, "Client 1" was convicted
OL,19,Fof money laundering and aggravated tax
OL,20,Ffraud by a European court and
OL,21,Fsentenced to four years in prison.
